 * Project: TrekRoll
 * Description: TikTok-inspired short video travel platform built as a web app.
 * Framework: Next.js 14+ (App Router with Turbopack)
 * Language: TypeScript
 * Styling: Tailwind CSS
 * Component Library: shadcn
 * State Management: Zustand
 * Form Handling: React Hook Form + Zod
 * Data Fetching: TanStack Query
 * Internationalization: next-intl (English & Burmese)
 * Routing: App Router (No src dir)
 * Fonts: Utility classes only (heading-h1 to h6, body-xs to lg). Add more font classes if necessary

 - Use aliases via `@/*`
 - Use `next-intl` for text content
 - Stick to TanStack Query for all data-fetching logic
 - Skeleton UI + Empty + Error states for every async fetch
 - Prefer Zustand for global state
 - Always use font utility classes, avoid hard-coded styles
 - Shadcan package is called shadcn, not shadcn-ui
 - If a component or a page file become too long separate new components (Max line 300)
 - Write a unit test after a feature is implemented